%S A396221 0,0,0,0,2284,3705940,1491290420
%N A396221 Number of relations R on an n-element set such that the transitive closure of R has exactly nine elements more than R.
%C A396221 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of binary relations R on an n-set for which exactly nine ordered pairs must be adjoined to obtain a transitive relation; i.e., |closure(R) \ R| = 9.
%e A396221 For n <= 3 we have n^2 <= 9, so a relation differing from its closure by nine pairs would have to be empty with full closure, which is impossible. Hence a(0) = a(1) = a(2) = a(3) = 0.
%Y A396221 Cf. A006905, A395083, A395919, A395920, A396053, A396054, A396055.
